{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775832779470,"sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","part":{"id":"prt_d77e1c76f001ClMbgx5P0ZpNCM","messageID":"msg_d77e1bb05001adzd7C521uIzhS","sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e92b6bd9f88943f8be33041d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n2: \n3: AR: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n4: Module: pkg/store\n5: Language: Go\n6: Size: S\n7: \n8: Specs:\n9: --- deployment/client-go.md ---\n10: # client-go library\n11: \n12: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n13: \n14: ## Clientset\n15: \n16: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n17: \n18: ```go\n19: type Interface interface {\n20: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n21: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n22: }\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### `Clientset` struct\n26: \n27: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n28: \n29: **Constructors**\n30: \n31: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n32: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n33: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n34: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n35: \n36: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n41: \n42: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n43: \n44: ```go\n45: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n46: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n47: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n48: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n49: }\n50: ```\n51: \n52: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n53: \n54: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n55: \n56: ```go\n57: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n58: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n59: }\n60: \n61: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n62: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n63: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n64: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n65: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n66: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n67: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n68: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n69: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n70: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n71: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n76: \n77: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n78: \n79: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n80: \n81: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n82: \n83: ```go\n84: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n85: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n86: ```\n87: \n88: (Empty — reserved for custom methods.)\n89: \n90: ### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n91: \n92: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` — test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n97: \n98: | File | Role |\n99: |------|------|\n100: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n101: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## Informer factory\n106: \n107: ### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n108: \n109: ```go\n110: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n111: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n112: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n113: \tShutdown()\n114: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n115: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n116: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n117: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n118: }\n119: ```\n120: \n121: **Constructors / options**\n122: \n123: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n124: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n125: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n126: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n127: \n128: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n129: \n130: ```go\n131: type Interface interface {\n132: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n133: }\n134: ```\n135: \n136: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n137: \n138: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n139: \n140: ```go\n141: type Interface interface {\n142: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n143: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n144: }\n145: ```\n146: \n147: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n148: \n149: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n150: \n151: ```go\n152: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n153: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n154: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n155: }\n156: ```\n157: \n158: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n159: \n160: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n161: \n162: `ForResource` switches on:\n163: \n164: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n165: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n166: \n167: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n171: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n172: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n173: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n174: }\n175: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n181: \n182: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n183: \n184: ```go\n185: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n186: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n187: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n188: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n189: }\n190: \n191: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n192: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n193: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n194: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n195: }\n196: ```\n197: \n198: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n199: \n200: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n201: \n202: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n203: \n204: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n205: \n206: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n211: \n212: | File | Role |\n213: |------|------|\n214: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` — in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n215: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n216: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n221: \n222: | Path | Role |\n223: |------|------|\n224: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n225: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n226: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n227: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n228: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n229: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n230: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n231: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n232: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n233: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n234: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n235: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n236: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n237: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n238: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n239: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n240: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n241: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n242: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n243: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n244: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n245: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n246: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n247: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n248: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n249: \n250: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n251: \n252: \n253: --- session-store/design.md ---\n254: # Session Store — Design\n255: \n256: ## Module\n257: \n258: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n259: \n260: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n261: \n262: ### Store interface (exact signatures)\n263: \n264: ```go\n265: package store\n266: \n267: import (\n268:     \"context\"\n269:     \"time\"\n270: \n271:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n272: )\n273: \n274: type Store interface {\n275:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n276:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n277:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n278:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n279:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n280:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n281:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n282:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n283:     Close() error\n284: }\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ### Errors\n288: \n289: ```go\n290: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ### Provider type constants (`singleton.go`)\n294: \n295: ```go\n296: const (\n297:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n298:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n299: )\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ### Singleton\n303: \n304: ```go\n305: var (\n306:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n307:     provider      Store\n308: )\n309: \n310: func Storage() Store\n311: func initStore() error\n312: ```\n313: \n314: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n315: \n316: ### Sandbox document type\n317: \n318: Stored JSON unmarshals to `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n319: \n320: ```go\n321: type SandboxInfo struct {\n322:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n323:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n324:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n325:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n326:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n327:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n328:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n329:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n330:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n331: }\n332: \n333: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n334:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n335:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n336:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n337: }\n338: ```\n339: \n340: ## Redis implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n341: \n342: ### Struct\n343: \n344: ```go\n345: type redisStore struct {\n346:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n347:     sessionPrefix        string\n348:     expiryIndexKey       string\n349:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n350: }\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Fixed key patterns\n354: \n355: | Field | Value |\n356: |-------|--------|\n357: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n358: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n359: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n360: \n361: ### Connection options (`makeRedisOptions`)\n362: \n363: ```go\n364: return &redisv9.Options{\n365:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // REDIS_ADDR\n366:     Password: redisPassword, // REDIS_PASSWORD\n367: }, nil\n368: ```\n369: \n370: ### Environment variables (Redis)\n371: \n372: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n373: |----------|----------|--------|\n374: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | |\n375: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n376: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default `redis` |\n377: \n378: ### Operations summary\n379: \n380: | Method | Redis commands |\n381: |--------|----------------|\n382: | `Ping` | `PING` → expect `PONG` |\n383: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n384: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n385: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n386: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n387: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n388: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n389: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n390: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n391: \n392: - `List*` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`.\n393: - `sessionKey(id)` → `sessionPrefix + sessionID`.\n394: \n395: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n396: \n397: ### Struct\n398: \n399: ```go\n400: type valkeyStore struct {\n401:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n402:     sessionPrefix        string\n403:     expiryIndexKey       string\n404:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n405: }\n406: ```\n407: \n408: Same string constants as Redis for prefix and ZSET keys.\n409: \n410: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n411: \n412: ```go\n413: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n414:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n415:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n416: }\n417: ```\n418: \n419: Optional: `DisableCache` from `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, must be true); `ForceSingleClient` from `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, must be true).\n420: \n421: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n422: \n423: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n424: |----------|----------|--------|\n425: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list → `InitAddress` |\n426: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n427: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n428: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n429: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n430: \n431: ### Operations summary\n432: \n433: | Method | Valkey API |\n434: |--------|------------|\n435: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n436: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n437: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n438: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n439: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n440: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n441: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n442: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n443: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n444: \n445: ### ZSET score semantics\n446: \n447: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store.\n448: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`; `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n449: \n450: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n451: \n452: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` builds all `session:{id}` keys and uses single `Mget`; comment states keys should be in same slot (deployment consideration).\n453: \n454: ## Dependencies (store package imports)\n455: \n456: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n457: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n458: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n459: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n460: \n461: \n462: --- session-store/spec.md ---\n463: # Session Store Specification\n464: \n465: ## Purpose\n466: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n467: \n468: ## Requirements\n469: \n470: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n471: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n474: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n475: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n476: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n477: \n478: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n479: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n482: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n483: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n484: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n485: \n486: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n487: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: Key construction\n490: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n491: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n492: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n493: \n494: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n495: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n498: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n499: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n500: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n501: \n502: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n503: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n504: \n505: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n506: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n507: - **WHEN** executed\n508: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n509: \n510: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n511: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n514: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n515: - **WHEN** called\n516: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n517: \n518: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n519: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n520: \n521: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n522: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n523: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n524: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n525: \n526: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n527: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: Full removal\n530: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n531: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n532: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n533: \n534: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n535: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n538: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n539: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n540: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n541: \n542: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n543: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n544: \n545: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n546: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n547: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n548: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n549: \n550: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n551: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n552: \n553: #### Scenario: Default redis\n554: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n555: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n556: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n557: \n558: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n559: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n560: \n561: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n562: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n563: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n564: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n565: \n566: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n567: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n568: \n569: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n570: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n571: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n572: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n573: \n574: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n575: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n576: \n577: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n578: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n579: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n580: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n581: \n582: \n583: Previous proposal:\n584: [Stage ST-1 completed]\n585: \n586: Include: architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy.\n\n(End of file - total 586 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n\nAR: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\nModule: pkg/store\nLanguage: Go\nSize: S\n\nSpecs:\n--- deployment/client-go.md ---\n# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n## Clientset\n\n### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775832779435,"end":1775832779468}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775832779519,"sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","part":{"id":"prt_d77e1cae4001RbZxrQpgAxMp6d","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d77e1bb05001adzd7C521uIzhS","sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":15547,"input":15441,"output":73,"reasoning":33,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.004436722}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775832781377,"sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","part":{"id":"prt_d77e1d23e001zyXNVChhcdEyVa","messageID":"msg_d77e1cb1b001Dn2t2euDfEYiIa","sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775832949456,"sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","part":{"id":"prt_d77e1e627001rE7H1naRbOGQsf","messageID":"msg_d77e1cb1b001Dn2t2euDfEYiIa","sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_42172ff135ee4b69b7a5e7e8","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-012: Session Store Interface Definition — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design defines the `pkg/store` package for AgentCube, providing a pluggable session storage abstraction with Redis and Valkey backends. The store persists sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, maintains sorted-set indices for expiry and activity-based garbage collection, and exposes a thread-safe singleton accessor.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Caller (Controller)                   │\n└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   store.Storage()                        │\n│              (sync.Once singleton accessor)              │\n└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n              ┌──────────┴──────────┐\n              ▼                     ▼\n┌───────────────────────┐ ┌───────────────────────┐\n│     redisStore        │ │     valkeyStore       │\n│  (go-redis/v9)        │ │  (valkey-io/valkey)   │\n└───────────┬───────────┘ └───────────┬───────────┘\n            │                         │\n            ▼                         ▼\n┌───────────────────────┐ ┌───────────────────────┐\n│       Redis           │ │       Valkey          │\n│  session:{id} (JSON)  │ │  session:{id} (JSON)  │\n│  session:expiry (ZSET)│ │  session:expiry (ZSET)│\n│  session:last_activity│ │  session:last_activity│\n└───────────────────────┘ └───────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Provider Selection Flow\n\n```\nSTORE_TYPE (env)\n    │\n    ├── unset / \"redis\"  → redisStore\n    ├── \"valkey\"         → valkeyStore\n    └── other            → initStore() error\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Store Interface\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\n// Store defines the contract for session-backed sandbox metadata persistence.\ntype Store interface {\n    // Ping verifies backend connectivity.\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n\n    // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox metadata by session ID.\n    // Returns ErrNotFound if the session key does not exist.\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // StoreSandbox atomically persists a new sandbox entry.\n    // Fails if sandbox is nil or ExpiresAt is zero.\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\n    // UpdateSandbox updates the JSON value for an existing session key.\n    // Does not modify ZSET indices. Returns error if key does not exist.\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\n    // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes the session key and all ZSET entries.\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n\n    // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes whose expiry time is before the given timestamp.\n    // Returns nil, nil when limit <= 0.\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes whose last activity is before the given timestamp.\n    // Returns nil, nil when limit <= 0.\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the activity index for a session.\n    // Returns ErrNotFound if the session key does not exist.\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n\n    // Close releases backend resources.\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\nvar (\n    // ErrNotFound is returned when a requested session key does not exist.\n    ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n)\n```\n\n### Singleton State\n\n```go\nvar (\n    initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n    provider      Store\n)\n\n// Storage returns the globally initialized Store instance.\n// Panics via klog.Fatalf if initialization fails.\nfunc Storage() Store {\n    initStoreOnce.Do(func() {\n        if err := initStore(); err != nil {\n            klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)\n        }\n    })\n    return provider\n}\n\nfunc initStore() error {\n    storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n    if storeType == \"\" {\n        storeType = redisStoreType\n    }\n    switch storeType {\n    case redisStoreType:\n        s, err := newRedisStore()\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        provider = s\n    case valkeyStoreType:\n        s, err := newValkeyStore()\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        provider = s\n    default:\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %q\", storeType)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Provider Type Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    redisStoreType  = \"redis\"\n    valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"\n)\n```\n\n### Sandbox Document Type\n\nMaps to `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo` — stored as JSON in the backend:\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Redis Implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n\n### Struct Definition\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Key Constants\n\n| Field                  | Value                    | Purpose                              |\n|------------------------|--------------------------|--------------------------------------|\n| `sessionPrefix`        | `\"session:\"`             | Prefix for session JSON string keys  |\n| `expiryIndexKey`       | `\"session:expiry\"`       | ZSET key for expiry-based GC         |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"`| ZSET key for activity-based GC       |\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc newRedisStore() (*redisStore, error) {\n    redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n    if redisAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n\n    redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if redisPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n\n    opts := &redisv9.Options{\n        Addr:     redisAddr,\n        Password: redisPassword,\n    }\n\n    cli := redisv9.NewClient(opts)\n    if err := cli.Ping(context.Background()).Err(); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"redis ping failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    return &redisStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Method Implementations\n\n#### Ping\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n    pong, err := rs.cli.Ping(ctx).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if pong != \"PONG\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %q\", pong)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### sessionKey helper\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n#### GetSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    data, err := rs.cli.Get(ctx, rs.sessionKey(sessionID)).Bytes()\n    if err == redisv9.Nil {\n        return nil, ErrNotFound\n    }\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n    if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &sandbox); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return &sandbox, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### StoreSandbox\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandbox == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n    if sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n    }\n\n    data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    key := rs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n    now := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n    expiryScore := float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n\n    pipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n    pipe.SetNX(ctx, key, data, 0)\n    pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: expiryScore, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n    pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: now, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n\n    _, err = pipe.Exec(ctx)\n    return err\n}\n```\n\n#### UpdateSandbox\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandbox == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n\n    data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    key := rs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n    ok, err := rs.cli.SetXX(ctx, key, data, 0).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if !ok {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n    key := rs.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    pipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n    pipe.Del(ctx, key)\n    pipe.ZRem(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, sessionID)\n    pipe.ZRem(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, sessionID)\n    _, err := pipe.Exec(ctx)\n    return err\n}\n```\n\n#### ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if limit <= 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    sessionIDs, err := rs.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, &redisv9.ZRangeBy{\n        Min:   \"-inf\",\n        Max:   fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()),\n        Count: limit,\n    }).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    return rs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n}\n```\n\n#### ListInactiveSandboxes\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if limit <= 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    sessionIDs, err := rs.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, &redisv9.ZRangeBy{\n        Min:   \"-inf\",\n        Max:   fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()),\n        Count: limit,\n    }).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    return rs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n}\n```\n\n#### loadSandboxesBySessionIDs (shared loader)\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n    for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n        keys[i] = rs.sessionKey(id)\n    }\n\n    results, err := rs.cli.MGet(ctx, keys...).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, raw := range results {\n        if raw == nil {\n            continue // orphan ZSET member, skip\n        }\n        data, ok := raw.(string)\n        if !ok || data == \"\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n        }\n        sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n    }\n    return sandboxes, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n    if sessionID == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")\n    }\n\n    key := rs.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    exists, err := rs.cli.Exists(ctx, key).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if exists == 0 {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n\n    if at.IsZero() {\n        at = time.Now()\n    }\n\n    return rs.cli.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redisv9.Z{\n        Score:  float64(at.Unix()),\n        Member: sessionID,\n    }).Err()\n}\n```\n\n#### Close\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) Close() error {\n    return rs.cli.Close()\n}\n```\n\n## Valkey Implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n\n### Struct Definition\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc newValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, error) {\n    valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n\n    valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if valkeyPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n\n    opts := &valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n        Password:    valkeyPassword,\n    }\n\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n            opts.DisableCache = true\n        }\n    }\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n            opts.ForceSingleClient = true\n        }\n    }\n\n    cli, err := valkey.NewClient(opts)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"create valkey client: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    // Verify connectivity\n    pong, err := cli.Do(context.Background(), cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n    if err != nil || pong != \"PONG\" {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"valkey ping failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    klog.V(2).Infof(\"valkey client initialized: addr=%s, disableCache=%v, forceSingle=%v\",\n        valkeyAddr, opts.DisableCache, opts.ForceSingleClient)\n\n    return &valkeyStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Method Implementations\n\n#### Ping\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n    pong, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if pong != \"PONG\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %q\", pong)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### sessionKey helper\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return vs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n#### GetSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    key := vs.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    resp, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()).AsBytes()\n    if err != nil {\n        if valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n            return nil, ErrNotFound\n        }\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n    if err := json.Unmarshal(resp, &sandbox); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return &sandbox, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### StoreSandbox\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandbox == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n    if sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n    }\n\n    data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    key := vs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n    now := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n    expiryScore := float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n\n    results := vs.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n        vs.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build(),\n        vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(expiryScore), sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n        vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(now, sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n    )\n\n    for _, result := range results {\n        if err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### UpdateSandbox\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandbox == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n\n    data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    key := vs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n    resp, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()).ToString()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if resp != \"OK\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n    results := vs.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n        vs.cli.B().Del().Key(vs.sessionKey(sessionID)).Build(),\n        vs.cli.B().Zrem().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n        vs.cli.B().Zrem().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n    )\n\n    for _, result := range results {\n        if err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if limit <= 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    resp, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).\n        Min(\"-inf\").\n        Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).\n        Limit().Offset(0).Count(limit).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    return vs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, resp)\n}\n```\n\n#### ListInactiveSandboxes\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if limit <= 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    resp, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).\n        Min(\"-inf\").\n        Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).\n        Limit().Offset(0).Count(limit).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    return vs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, resp)\n}\n```\n\n#### loadSandboxesBySessionIDs (shared loader)\n\n> **Note:** Keys should be in the same slot for cluster deployments to use MGET efficiently.\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n    for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n        keys[i] = vs.sessionKey(id)\n    }\n\n    // MGET all keys in one command\n    results, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, data := range results {\n        if data == \"\" {\n            continue // orphan ZSET member or missing key, skip\n        }\n        var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n        }\n        sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n    }\n    return sandboxes, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n    if sessionID == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")\n    }\n\n    key := vs.sessionKey(sessionID)\n\n    // Check existence\n    exists, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build()).AsInt64()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if exists == 0 {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n\n    if at.IsZero() {\n        at = time.Now()\n    }\n\n    return vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).\n        ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID).Build()).Error()\n}\n```\n\n#### Close\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n    vs.cli.Close()\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n### Redis\n\n| Variable                 | Required | Default | Description                                    |\n|--------------------------|----------|---------|------------------------------------------------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR`             | Yes      | —       | Redis server address (`host:port`)             |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD`         | Yes*     | —       | Authentication password                        |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`| No       | `true`  | Set to `false` (case-insensitive) to disable   |\n| `STORE_TYPE`             | No       | `redis` | Must be `redis` for this backend               |\n\n### Valkey\n\n| Variable                   | Required | Default | Description                                    |\n|----------------------------|----------|---------|------------------------------------------------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR`              | Yes      | —       | Comma-separated Valkey addresses               |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD`          | Yes*     | —       | Authentication password                        |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No       | `true`  | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`     | No       | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching   |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE`      | No       | `false` | Set to `true` to force single client mode      |\n| `STORE_TYPE`               | Yes      | —       | Must be `valkey` for this backend              |\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Scenario                          | Error Returned               | Notes                                        |\n|-----------------------------------|------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|\n| Session key not found             | `ErrNotFound`                | Both backends normalize to sentinel error    |\n| Nil sandbox passed to StoreSandbox| `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")`| Input validation                             |\n| Zero ExpiresAt                    | `errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")` | Input validation              |\n| Empty sessionID                   | `errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")` | UpdateSessionLastActivity precondition  |\n| UpdateSandbox on missing key      | `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` | SET XX returns false/!OK           |\n| Pipeline command failure          | Wrapped backend error        | Any command in batch failing aborts all      |\n| Unsupported STORE_TYPE            | `fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %q\", storeType)` | initStore validation         |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test File              | Coverage                                          |\n|------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|\n| `store_test.go`        | Singleton initialization, provider selection      |\n| `store_redis_test.go`  | Redis implementation methods with mock client     |\n| `store_valkey_test.go` | Valkey implementation methods with mock client    |\n\n### Test Cases\n\n#### Singleton & Provider Selection\n\n| Test Name                          | Description                                    |\n|------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|\n| `TestStorage_DefaultsToRedis`      | Unset STORE_TYPE → redisStore                  |\n| `TestStorage_ValkeyProvider`       | STORE_TYPE=valkey → valkeyStore                |\n| `TestStorage_InvalidProvider`      | STORE_TYPE=unknown → initStore error           |\n| `TestStorage_ConcurrentAccess`     | Multiple goroutines → exactly one init         |\n\n#### Redis Implementation\n\n| Test Name                                  | Description                                    |\n|--------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|\n| `TestRedisStore_Ping_Success`              | PING → PONG                                    |\n| `TestRedisStore_Ping_Failure`              | Connection error → propagated                  |\n| `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found`| GET returns JSON → unmarshaled SandboxInfo     |\n| `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound`| GET nil → ErrNotFound                       |\n| `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success`      | Pipeline: SETNX + ZADD×2 succeed               |\n| `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected`  | nil sandbox → error                            |\n| `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry`   | Zero ExpiresAt → error                         |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_Success`     | SETXX → OK                                     |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey`  | SETXX → false → \"key not exists\" error         |\n| `TestRedisStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID`  | Pipeline: DEL + ZREM×2 succeed                 |\n| `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes`      | ZRANGEBYSCORE → MGET → filtered sandboxes      |\n| `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ZeroLimit`| limit=0 → nil, nil                          |\n| `TestRedisStore_ListInactiveSandboxes`     | ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity → sandboxes     |\n| `TestRedisStore_LoadSandboxes_SkipsOrphans`| MGET returns nil for orphan ZSET member → skip |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_Success`| EXISTS=1 → ZADD with timestamp          |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound`| EXISTS=0 → ErrNotFound                  |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime`| at.IsZero() → uses time.Now()            |\n| `TestRedisStore_Close`                     | cli.Close() called                             |\n\n#### Valkey Implementation\n\n| Test Name                                      | Description                                    |\n|------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|\n| `TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success`                 | Ping → PONG                                    |\n| `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found`  | Get → bytes → unmarshaled                      |\n| `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound`| IsValkeyNil → ErrNotFound                      |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success`         | DoMulti: SETNX + ZADD×2 succeed                |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_Success`        | SET XX → \"OK\"                                  |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey`     | SET XX → not \"OK\" → error                      |\n| `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID`     | DoMulti: DEL + ZREM×2 succeed                  |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes`         | Zrangebyscore → loadSandboxes                  |\n| `TestValkeyStore_LoadSandboxes_SkipsEmpty`     | MGET returns \"\" for missing key → skip         |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity`    | Exists=1 → Zadd                                |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Options_DisableCache`         | VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true → DisableCache set   |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Options_ForceSingle`          | VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true → ForceSingleClient   |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test Name                              | Description                                    |\n|----------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|\n| `TestRedisStore_Integration_FullLifecycle`| Store → Get → Update → List → Delete cycle  |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Integration_FullLifecycle`| Same cycle against real Valkey instance     |\n| `TestStore_GC_Workflow`                | Store expired sandboxes, list and delete       |\n\n### Mock Strategy\n\n- **Redis:** Use `go-redis/v9` compatible mock (e.g., `miniredis` or interface-based mocks)\n- **Valkey:** Use interface abstraction over `valkey.Client` with recorded command expectations\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go                  # Store interface, ErrNotFound, constants\n├── singleton.go              # Storage(), initStore(), sync.Once\n├── store_redis.go            # redisStore implementation\n├── store_valkey.go           # valkeyStore implementation\n├── store_test.go             # Singleton & provider selection tests\n├── store_redis_test.go       # Redis unit tests\n└── store_valkey_test.go      # Valkey unit tests\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Module                                    | Purpose                      |\n|-------------------------------------------|------------------------------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`            | Redis client                 |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`          | Valkey client                |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2`                          | Structured logging           |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definition |\n\n## Deployment Considerations\n\n1. **Valkey Cluster Slot Affinity:** The `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` method uses MGET which requires all keys to hash to the same slot in cluster mode. Consider using hash tags (e.g., `session:{cluster}:id`) if deploying to Valkey Cluster.\n\n2. **Password Policy:** By default, both backends require a password. Set `{BACKEND}_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments.\n\n3. **ZSET Index Growth:** The `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` sorted sets grow monotonically. Ensure the GC controller regularly calls `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` to prevent unbounded growth.\n\n4. **Connection Pooling:** Both clients use default connection pool settings. Tune via environment-specific configuration if needed (e.g., `REDIS_MAX_CONN`, `VALKEY_MAX_CONN`).\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775832949446,"end":1775832949453}}}}
