{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775833079024,"sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","part":{"id":"prt_d77e4960a001juuRc1XpHf230R","messageID":"msg_d77e484f8001U2YVr5VMywznn0","sessionID":"ses_2881e45edffefBIR6QnKk4Omhz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_4ec8b4ade887463c90fa3e05","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-012: Session Store Interface Definition — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pkg/store` package provides a pluggable session storage abstraction for AgentCube sandbox metadata. It persists sandbox information keyed by session ID, maintains sorted-set indices for expiry-based and activity-based garbage collection, and supports Redis or Valkey backends selected at runtime via `STORE_TYPE`.\n\n### 1.2 Provider Selection Flow\n\n```\nSTORE_TYPE (env, case-insensitive)\n    │\n    ├── unset / \"redis\"   → redisStore  (go-redis/v9)\n    ├── \"valkey\"          → valkeyStore (valkey-io/valkey-go)\n    └── other             → initStore() error\n```\n\n### 1.3 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│               Caller (GC Controller / Router)         │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n                       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  store.Storage()                      │\n│             (sync.Once singleton accessor)            │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n            ┌──────────┴──────────┐\n            ▼                     ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────┐\n│    redisStore       │ │    valkeyStore      │\n│  go-redis/v9        │ │  valkey-io/valkey   │\n└─────────┬───────────┘ └─────────┬───────────┘\n          │                       │\n          ▼                       ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────┐\n│      Redis          │ │      Valkey         │\n│ session:{id} (JSON) │ │ session:{id} (JSON) │\n│ session:expiry      │ │ session:expiry      │\n│  (ZSET: score=exp)  │ │  (ZSET: score=exp)  │\n│ session:last_activity│ │session:last_activity│\n│  (ZSET: score=ts)   │ │  (ZSET: score=ts)   │\n└─────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.4 Package Layout\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go                  # Store interface, ErrNotFound\n├── singleton.go              # Storage(), initStore(), sync.Once, type constants\n├── store_redis.go            # redisStore implementation\n├── store_valkey.go           # valkeyStore implementation\n├── store_test.go             # Singleton & provider selection tests\n├── store_redis_test.go       # Redis unit tests\n└── store_valkey_test.go      # Valkey unit tests\n```\n\n### 1.5 Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging (Valkey options, fatal init) |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` type definition |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Store Interface\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n### 2.3 Provider Type Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    redisStoreType  = \"redis\"\n    valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"\n)\n```\n\n### 2.4 Singleton State\n\n```go\nvar (\n    initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n    provider      Store\n)\n\nfunc Storage() Store\nfunc initStore() error\n```\n\n- `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error → `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n\n### 2.5 Sandbox Document Type\n\nStored as JSON, unmarshals to `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 2.6 Redis Implementation Struct\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### 2.7 Valkey Implementation Struct\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### 2.8 Key Constants (Both Implementations)\n\n| Field | Value | Purpose |\n|-------|-------|---------|\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session JSON string keys |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry-based GC |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity-based GC |\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Method Specifications\n\n#### Ping\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Redis | `PING` → expect `PONG` string response |\n| Valkey | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n| Error | Backend connection error propagated |\n\n#### GetSandboxBySessionID\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Key | `session:{sessionID}` |\n| Redis | `GET` → `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n| Valkey | `B().Get().Key(key)` → `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n| Success | JSON unmarshal → `*types.SandboxInfo` |\n\n#### StoreSandbox\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Validation | Reject nil sandbox; reject zero `ExpiresAt` |\n| Redis | Pipeline: `SETNX session:{id} <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <score> <id>`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now> <id>` |\n| Valkey | `DoMulti`: same three commands |\n| ZSET scores | Expiry: `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())`; Activity: `float64(time.Now().Unix())` |\n| Atomicity | All commands in one pipeline; any failure aborts batch |\n\n#### UpdateSandbox\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Redis | `SET key value XX` (key must exist); false → `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` |\n| Valkey | `SET ... XX`; response `ToString() != \"OK\"` → same error |\n| Side effects | Does NOT modify ZSET entries |\n\n#### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Redis | Pipeline: `DEL session:{id}`, `ZREM session:expiry {id}`, `ZREM session:last_activity {id}` |\n| Valkey | `DoMulti`: same three commands |\n\n#### ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Precondition | `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil` |\n| Redis | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 limit` → pipeline GETs |\n| Valkey | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` → `Mget` |\n| Missing keys | Orphan ZSET members (no corresponding JSON key) are skipped, not errors |\n\n#### ListInactiveSandboxes\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Same as ListExpiredSandboxes, but queries `session:last_activity` ZSET |\n\n#### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Validation | Reject empty `sessionID`; if `at.IsZero()` use `time.Now()` |\n| Precondition | Session key must exist; absent → `ErrNotFound` |\n| Redis | `EXISTS session:{id}` → must be 1; then `ZADD session:last_activity <score> <id>` |\n| Valkey | `Exists` → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n\n#### Close\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Redis | `cli.Close()` |\n| Valkey | `vs.cli.Close()` → return nil |\n\n### 3.2 ZSET Score Semantics\n\n| Index | Score Source | When Set |\n|-------|-------------|----------|\n| `session:expiry` | `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n| `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n| `session:last_activity` | `float64(at.Unix())` (or now if zero) | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n\n### 3.3 Error Handling Matrix\n\n| Scenario | Error Returned | Notes |\n|----------|---------------|-------|\n| Session key not found | `ErrNotFound` | Both backends normalize |\n| Nil sandbox to StoreSandbox | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` | Input validation |\n| Zero ExpiresAt | `errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")` | Input validation |\n| Empty sessionID | `errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")` | UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n| UpdateSandbox missing key | `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` | SET XX fails |\n| Pipeline command failure | Backend error | Batch aborts |\n| Unsupported STORE_TYPE | `fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %q\", storeType)` | initStore |\n| Missing REDIS_ADDR | `errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")` | Redis init |\n| Missing REDIS_PASSWORD | `errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required ...\")` | Unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| Missing VALKEY_ADDR | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")` | Valkey init |\n| Missing VALKEY_PASSWORD | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required ...\")` | Unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Implementation\n\n### 4.1 Singleton (`singleton.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc Storage() Store {\n    initStoreOnce.Do(func() {\n        if err := initStore(); err != nil {\n            klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)\n        }\n    })\n    return provider\n}\n\nfunc initStore() error {\n    storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n    if storeType == \"\" {\n        storeType = redisStoreType\n    }\n    switch storeType {\n    case redisStoreType:\n        s, err := newRedisStore()\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        provider = s\n    case valkeyStoreType:\n        s, err := newValkeyStore()\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        provider = s\n    default:\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %q\", storeType)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.2 Redis Constructor (`store_redis.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc newRedisStore() (*redisStore, error) {\n    redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n    if redisAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n\n    redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if redisPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n\n    opts := &redisv9.Options{\n        Addr:     redisAddr,\n        Password: redisPassword,\n    }\n\n    cli := redisv9.NewClient(opts)\n    if err := cli.Ping(context.Background()).Err(); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"redis ping failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    return &redisStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 Redis Key Helper\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n### 4.4 Redis StoreSandbox\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandbox == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n    if sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n    }\n\n    data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    key := rs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n    now := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n    expiryScore := float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n\n    pipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n    pipe.SetNX(ctx, key, data, 0)\n    pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: expiryScore, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n    pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: now, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n\n    _, err = pipe.Exec(ctx)\n    return err\n}\n```\n\n### 4.5 Redis Load Helper\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n    for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n        keys[i] = rs.sessionKey(id)\n    }\n\n    results, err := rs.cli.MGet(ctx, keys...).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, raw := range results {\n        if raw == nil {\n            continue\n        }\n        data, ok := raw.(string)\n        if !ok || data == \"\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n        }\n        sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n    }\n    return sandboxes, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.6 Valkey Constructor (`store_valkey.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc newValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, error) {\n    valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n\n    valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if valkeyPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n\n    opts := &valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n        Password:    valkeyPassword,\n    }\n\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n            opts.DisableCache = true\n        }\n    }\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n            opts.ForceSingleClient = true\n        }\n    }\n\n    cli, err := valkey.NewClient(opts)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"create valkey client: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    pong, err := cli.Do(context.Background(), cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n    if err != nil || pong != \"PONG\" {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"valkey ping failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    klog.V(2).Infof(\"valkey client initialized: addr=%s, disableCache=%v, forceSingle=%v\",\n        valkeyAddr, opts.DisableCache, opts.ForceSingleClient)\n\n    return &valkeyStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.7 Valkey Load Helper\n\n> **Note:** Keys should be in the same slot for cluster deployments to use MGET efficiently.\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n    for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n        keys[i] = vs.sessionKey(id)\n    }\n\n    results, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, data := range results {\n        if data == \"\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n        }\n        sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n    }\n    return sandboxes, nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Environment Variables\n\n### 5.1 Redis\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | — | Redis server address |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | — | Auth password |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `redis` for this backend |\n\n### 5.2 Valkey\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | — | Comma-separated → `InitAddress` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | — | Auth password |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | `\"true\"` → `DisableCache` |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | `\"true\"` → `ForceSingleClient` |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Yes | — | Must be `valkey` for this backend |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\n#### Singleton & Provider Selection (`store_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestStorage_DefaultsToRedis` | Unset `STORE_TYPE` → redisStore |\n| `TestStorage_ValkeyProvider` | `STORE_TYPE=valkey` → valkeyStore |\n| `TestStorage_InvalidProvider` | `STORE_TYPE=unknown` → initStore error |\n| `TestStorage_ConcurrentAccess` | Multiple goroutines → exactly one init |\n\n#### Redis Implementation (`store_redis_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestRedisStore_Ping_Success` | PING → PONG |\n| `TestRedisStore_Ping_Failure` | Connection error → propagated |\n| `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found` | GET returns JSON → unmarshaled |\n| `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | GET nil → `ErrNotFound` |\n| `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success` | Pipeline: SETNX + ZADD×2 succeed |\n| `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected` | nil sandbox → error |\n| `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` | Zero ExpiresAt → error |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` | SETXX → OK |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | SETXX → false → error |\n| `TestRedisStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: DEL + ZREM×2 |\n| `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` | ZRANGEBYSCORE → MGET → sandboxes |\n| `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ZeroLimit` | limit=0 → nil, nil |\n| `TestRedisStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` | ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity |\n| `TestRedisStore_LoadSandboxes_SkipsOrphans` | MGET nil → skip orphan ZSET member |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_Success` | EXISTS=1 → ZADD |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound` | EXISTS=0 → `ErrNotFound` |\n| `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` | `at.IsZero()` → uses `time.Now()` |\n| `TestRedisStore_Close` | `cli.Close()` called |\n\n#### Valkey Implementation (`store_valkey_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success` | Ping → PONG |\n| `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found` | Get → bytes → unmarshaled |\n| `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success` | DoMulti: SETNX + ZADD×2 |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` | SET XX → \"OK\" |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | SET XX → not \"OK\" → error |\n| `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | DoMulti: DEL + ZREM×2 |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` | Zrangebyscore → loadSandboxes |\n| `TestValkeyStore_LoadSandboxes_SkipsEmpty` | MGET \"\" → skip missing key |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity` | Exists=1 → Zadd |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Options_DisableCache` | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` → set |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Options_ForceSingle` | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` → set |\n\n### 6.2 Integration Tests\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestRedisStore_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Store → Get → Update → List → Delete against real Redis |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Same cycle against real Valkey |\n| `TestStore_GC_Workflow` | Store expired sandboxes, list and delete |\n\n### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n\n- **Redis:** Use `miniredis` for in-memory Redis-compatible testing\n- **Valkey:** Use interface abstraction over `valkey.Client` with recorded command expectations\n- All tests run with `-race` flag for data race detection\n\n### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n5. No sensitive data in logs (passwords, connection strings)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Deployment Considerations\n\n1. **Valkey Cluster Slot Affinity:** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` uses MGET which requires all keys to hash to the same slot in cluster mode. Consider hash tags (e.g., `session:{cluster}:id`) if deploying to Valkey Cluster.\n\n2. **Password Policy:** Both backends require a password by default. Set `{BACKEND}_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments.\n\n3. **ZSET Index Growth:** `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` sorted sets grow monotonically. Ensure the GC controller regularly calls `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` to prevent unbounded growth.\n\n4. **Connection Pooling:** Both clients use default connection pool settings. Tune via environment-specific configuration if needed.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Implementation Steps\n\n### Phase 1: Interface & Singleton (Day 1)\n\n1. Define `Store` interface in `store.go`\n2. Define `ErrNotFound` sentinel error\n3. Implement singleton pattern in `singleton.go` with provider selection\n4. Write `store_test.go` for singleton and provider selection\n\n### Phase 2: Redis Implementation (Day 2)\n\n1. Implement `redisStore` struct and constructor in `store_redis.go`\n2. Implement all Store interface methods\n3. Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n4. Write `store_redis_test.go` with miniredis\n\n### Phase 3: Valkey Implementation (Day 3)\n\n1. Implement `valkeyStore` struct and constructor in `store_valkey.go`\n2. Implement all Store interface methods\n3. Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n4. Write `store_valkey_test.go`\n\n### Phase 4: Integration & Gate (Day 4)\n\n1. Run `go build ./pkg/store/...`\n2. Run `go test ./pkg/store/... -v`\n3. Run `go test -race ./pkg/store/...`\n4. Verify no sensitive data in logs\n5. Fix all issues\n\n---\n\n## 9. Future Changes\n\n| Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n| AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Additional backend support (e.g., etcd, DynamoDB) | P3 |\n\n### Known Limitations\n\n- No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n- MGET in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` assumes single-slot keys for cluster deployments\n- No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n- Singleton pattern does not support re-initialization or hot-swapping backends\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775833078840,"end":1775833079021}}}}
